BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:M0BfiGrfOBztHrFpiVsM4
SUMMARY:SP 202: Fabric Printing PILOT *MEMBERS ONLY*
DTSTAMP:20260406T054320Z
DTSTART:20260411T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:This class is only available for VERA members. If you are looki
	ng to sign up for SP 202: Fabric Printing\, there is another class availab
	le for sign up on June 13th!\n\nDo you dream of people wearing your artwor
	k out on the streets? Want to make shirts for your friend’s music project?
	 Level up your fabric printing experience and take home your own printed t
	ote bag in this 3-hour intermediate-level fabric printing class! In this h
	ands-on workshop\, you’ll explore the use-cases for printing on fabric\, p
	ractice properly setting up on the t-shirt press\, and registering a 2-col
	or fabric print. Students will receive three shirts to print on (sizes S—3
	XL are available). Students will be printing a Vera specific design\, excl
	usive to the 202 class.\n\nStudents must complete Screenprint 101 before a
	ttending this class.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/L3b0e578a8c6\n\nFrom The Vera
	 Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/L3b0e578a8c6
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7yOtszbL7CxhthLqAegyG
SUMMARY:LS 301: Front of House Mixing
DTSTAMP:20260406T054320Z
DTSTART:20260411T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:The final course of VERA’s Live Sound series\, this three-hour 
	workshop includes practice mixing a live band in a low pressure environmen
	t\, starting with the basics of soundcheck and ending with a full blown mi
	x. Subject matter will include: Setting up a front of house mix on an M32 
	board\, preamps\, EQ settings\, mixing styles for different genres\, sound
	 pressure levels\, outboard gear techniques and lots of critical listening
	 to ensure that show attendees\, artists\, and staff have a great experien
	ce at the show.\n\nStudents must complete both LS 201: Small PA Mixing and
	 LS 202: Mixing for Monitors before you can take this class.\n\nThis class
	 is a prerequisite for shadowing and ultimately becoming the Lead Sound En
	gineer at Vera Project shows. Each Live Sound class unlocks new audio engi
	neering volunteer shifts at Vera and eventually paid opportunities in and 
	outside of the venue. Become a volunteer at Vera to access other audio-rel
	ated educational programs such as tours\, field trips\, and internships.\n
	\nhttps://link.dice.fm/h1f36efac95d\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/h1f36efac95d
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
