BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3RW3TpkDgC8yTdp6vleE0
SUMMARY:Silent Reading Night
DTSTAMP:20260406T054320Z
DTSTART:20260416T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Silent Reading Night – April Edition \\nDate: Thursday\\\, Apri
	l 16th \\nTime: 6:00 PM – 9:00 PM \\nTheme: Poetic Words \\nWe wanted to c
	elebrate National Poetry Month with a poetry themed silent reading night! 
	Open Books: A Poem Emporium will be tabling for this event. \\nEvent Activ
	ities: \\nStill TBD! Check back later! \\n \\n \\nEvent Itinerary \\n6:00 
	PM – Mix & Mingle \\n\\nGrab a cup of tea and settle in.\\nMeet fellow rea
	ders and share what book you’re currently enjoying.\\nBYOM – Bring Your Ow
	n Mug! Hot water will be available.\\n\\n6:30 PM – Silent Reading Begins \
	\n\\nSettle into your cozy reading spot and dive into your book.\\nEnjoy t
	he quiet atmosphere of reading in community.\\n\\n7:30 PM – Reading Break 
	\\n\\nChat with your neighbor! Ask them what they are reading.\\nGrab a sn
	ack or drink at the bar\\nCheck out Open Books: A Poem Emporium's book tab
	le\\n\\n7:40 PM – Break Ends \\n\\nHead back to the Lapis Theater and do m
	ore reading.\\n\\n8:30 PM – Social Time & Book Chats \\n\\nShare thoughts 
	on your reads\\\, favorite passages\\\, or just connect with fellow book l
	overs.\\n\\n9:00 PM – Event Concludes \\n \\nThis is our monthly Silent Re
	ading Night\\\, each month we will have a new theme to inspire your readin
	g. Rediscover the joy of reading in good company at the Hugo House. \\nWe 
	can’t wait to read with you! \\nFree admission to this event is made possi
	ble with support from 4Culture.\n\nhttps://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-16
	/\n\nFrom Hugo House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-16/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
